### Defaults (when no project conventions are specified)

- Use TypeScript with strict mode enabled
- ES module syntax with `.js` extensions in imports
- Use `node:` prefix for built-in modules
- Prefer `const` over `let`, never use `var`
- Use early returns to reduce nesting
- Name files in kebab-case
- Name interfaces/types in PascalCase
- Name functions/variables in camelCase
- Write JSDoc comments for all public APIs
- Keep functions under 50 lines when possible
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Handle errors explicitly, never swallow exceptions

